The paper deals with a combinatorial problem (stable matching) and provides a new upper bound on the maximum number of stable matchings. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses a reduction to counting the number of downsets of a family of posets, which is a common technique in algorithms and computational complexity. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
